Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/description/DescribedThing
Object: A thing that has a description.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/description/
Object: A model describing the connection between a thing having a description and the thing providing that description, for example: a procedure as described by an item of legislation, or a procedure route as described by a Standing Order.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/description/describedBy
Object: Relates a thing that has a description to a thing that provides that description.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/description/DescribingThing
Object: A thing that provides a description.
